Larry King, Matt Lauer, Greta Van Susteren - they all wanted Debra Lafave, the former Tampa teacher accused of seducing a teenage boy.
Even a judge's gag order could not put the blue-eyed blonde and her media magnet lawyer back in the box.
Finally, the boy's family could take no more.
They pulled the plug on prosecution, agreeing Tuesday to a plea deal that will keep the former Greco Middle School teacher out of prison.
